imdb.title: One Punch Man: Wanpanman
imdb.plot: The story of Saitama, a hero that does it just for fun & can defeat his enemies with a single punch.

episodes.title: A Super Serious Look Back!
episodes.plot: Learn the history of One-Punch Man, and get ready for season 2 with a super serious recap.

episodes.title: Return of the Hero
episodes.plot: Saitama and Genos are out shopping when they come across G4, a demonic robot on a mission to eliminate King. Meanwhile, Sitch attempts to recruit various assassins and villains.

episodes.title: Human Monster
episodes.plot: Garou issues a declaration of war on the Hero Association through terrifying means, Hellish Blizzard gives Saitama an ultimatum, and Genos decides to eliminate his master's stalker, Speed-o'.

episodes.title: The Hunt Begins
episodes.plot: Garou attacks the S-rank hero Tank top Master, his followers, and Mumen Rider. Garou continues his pursuit of attacking heroes. Saitama buys a wig to join a martial arts tournament after having a brief exchange with Garou.

episodes.title: Metal Bat
episodes.plot: Assigned to guard a VIP and his son, Metal Bat couldn't be less thrilled. But when the group is suddenly attacked all hell breaks loose. Meanwhile, Saitama has disguised himself as Charanko in order to enter the "Super Fight" martial arts tournament.

episodes.title: The Martial Arts Tournament
episodes.plot: Metal bat fights Garo. A lot of monsters surface around multiple cities and it is difficult for all the heroes to fight them. Meanwhile, Saitama is at the tournament and Genos is in the audience.

episodes.title: The Uprising of the Monsters
episodes.plot: Saitama continues facing opponents in the tournament. Genos receives a stress signal depicting that there are 5 monsters in City C and goes to kill them. Blizzard tries to fight a monster but she turns out be very strong.

episodes.title: Class S Heroes
episodes.plot: As the Super Fight tournament heads for its grand finale, the Class S heroes battle to hold back the tide of monster incursions. Meanwhile, Atomic Samurai is setting in motion a plan of his own.

episodes.title: The Resistance of the Strong
episodes.plot: Goketsu, the first Super Fight Tournament champion, arrives in the stadium. Having now become a monster, he's aiming to force the Super Fight competitors to turn into monsters themselves. When several do, it's up to Suiryu to take them on alone.

episodes.title: The Troubles of the Strongest
episodes.plot: Saitama returns to the battle, but is starting to get through a gloomy state because of an obvious reason.

episodes.title: The Encircling Net of Justice
episodes.plot: The Monster Association invited all of the S-Class heroes to their hideout in City Z. Meanwhile, Garo encounters a serious threat.

episodes.title: Everyone's Dignity
episodes.plot: Garou continues his fight against the A Class heroes while some prominent S Class heroes make special entrances.

episodes.title: Cleaning Up the Disciple's Mess
episodes.plot: As the fight continues between Garou and his former master, Bang, a prominent threat from the Monster Association reappears.

episodes.title: The Strongest Man
episodes.plot: Saitama is a guy who's a hero for fun. After saving a child from certain death, he decided to become a hero, training hard for three years.

episodes.title: The Lone Cyborg
episodes.plot: A monster is moving toward City Z--one that has been created by the mysterious organization known as The House of Evolution.

episodes.title: The Obsessive Scientist
episodes.plot: Saitama and Genos glean information about the House of Evolution and its founder, Dr. Genus.

episodes.title: The Modern Ninja
episodes.plot: A group of Bald thugs use body armors to terrorize rich people. Sonic Speed, a hired ninja fights them. Unfortunately he meets with Saitama who is also a Bald.

episodes.title: The Ultimate Mentor
episodes.plot: Determined to get a little recognition, Saitama decides to become a pro hero, but first, he must pass the Hero Association tests and become a full-fledged member.

episodes.title: The Terrifying City
episodes.plot: To remain on the "Hero" list Saitama has to show some activity in every week. Currently the City Z is defined as the 'ghost town'. Heroes are gathered together to find out whats going on.

episodes.title: The Ultimate Disciple
episodes.plot: A giant meteor threatens to destroy City Z. All S-Rank heroes are called to City Z to destroy the meteor before its collision.

episodes.title: The Deep Sea King
episodes.plot: Several Sea Folk appear and begin attacking citizens. They are easily defeated until The Deep Sea King appears and defeats many heroes including an S-Class.

episodes.title: Unyielding Justice
episodes.plot: The fight with the Deep Sea King concludes and Saitama and Genos reflect on it as well as Saitama's promotion to B-Class.

episodes.title: Unparalleled Peril
episodes.plot: Saitama and all class S heroes are gathered together to be informed of an imminent extremely danger threat.

episodes.title: The Dominator of the Universe
episodes.plot: An alien conqueror lands in a spaceship to conquer the Earth during the S class heroes meeting.

episodes.title: The Strongest Hero
episodes.plot: Saitama takes on the alien leader in epic battle as the S class heroes fight the alien warriors and destroy the spaceship.
